# Safety-Critical Workflow — sync hub + immutable audit + tested DR

> **Project:** {{ .ProjectPrefix }}
> **Generated by:** mtix {{ .Version }}
> **Workflow audience:** regulated teams (aerospace, medical, defense,
> finance) that need an attributable audit trail and a tested disaster
> recovery procedure.

> **Trust banner.** The sync hub is a replication mechanism, not a
> tenancy boundary. Anyone with the hub DSN can read every event ever
> pushed. The mitigations in this workflow narrow the trust surface
> but do not eliminate it.

This workflow extends the [small-team workflow](small-team.md) with
controls regulated adopters typically require:

- **Hub backup archived to immutable cold storage** so the audit
  trail survives a malicious PG superuser.
- **Daemon-as-service** on every developer's machine so un-pushed
  events do not pile up locally beyond the daemon's interval.
- **Server-side enforcement** of snapshot freshness so a developer
  cannot bypass the pre-push hook with `git push --no-verify`.
- **Documented and rehearsed disaster recovery** for hub loss and
  for individual CLI loss.

mtix gives you the primitives. Workflow and policy decisions
(retention duration, hosting, escalation, distinct authorIDs per
agent) belong to your team's compliance owner.

