## Failure modes

| What can go wrong | How mtix behaves | What you do |
|---|---|---|
| **Hub unreachable** during push | Push errors with a redacted message; `meta.sync.consecutive_errors` bumps. Daemon retries on next tick. In hook mode, warns and skips so `git push` is not blocked. | Restore connectivity; daemon catches up. |
| **Hub unreachable** consecutive ≥ 3 | `mtix_sync_workflow` MCP tool reports `hub-unreachable`. | Run `mtix sync doctor`; verify TLS / DSN / connectivity. |
| **Lost laptop with un-pushed events** | Local pending events die with the machine. | Daemon mitigates by pushing every 30s. Un-pushed events at the moment of loss are unrecoverable — document this as accepted risk in your team's compliance evidence. |
| **Hook bypassed client-side** (`git push --no-verify`) | Server-side enforcement rejects the push. | No remediation needed; the server-side check is the gate. |
| **Daemon stops running** | No periodic pull/push; local queue grows. | Add a monitoring check (`systemctl is-active mtix-sync`) to your alerting; alert on `inactive`. |
| **Schema mismatch** (developer running an older binary) | Sync operations refuse with a structured error mentioning the schema version. | Pin the team's mtix binary version in your dev env documentation; gate upgrades through the same change management you use for code. |
| **Queue full** (`sync.max_queue_size` cap) | `ErrSyncQueueFull` returned to the caller of `mtix create`/`update`. Event NOT silently dropped. | Run `mtix sync push --force` to drain; or raise the cap. |
| **PG superuser disables triggers** | `audit_log` is mutable. mtix has no in-process detection. | Mitigated by the immutable backup archive: the cold-storage copy is the canonical history. Detect via routine archive-vs-hub comparison. |
| **Hub backup upload fails** | Local SQL file remains on the operator machine. | Monitor your upload job; alert on failure. Do not delete the local file until upload is confirmed. |
| **DSN leaked** | Every error / log / panic flows through `redact.DSN`; the DSN itself does not leak via mtix. But possession of the DSN by an attacker is still possession. | Rotate the PG password immediately; revoke the leaked role; review `pg_stat_activity` for unfamiliar sessions. |
| **Divergent history** (two hubs initialized with the same project prefix) | `DetectDivergentHistory` returns `ErrSyncDivergentHistory` on init. | Compliance impact: the local history may have entries not on the new hub. Use `mtix sync reconcile --import-as PARENT-ID` to graft local nodes; document the divergence in compliance evidence. |
| **PG provider compromise** | Out of mtix scope. | Use a provider with documented security posture. The cold-storage backup is your tamper-evidence anchor. |

